result.name: Marbling

reviews.text:
My wife and I ate there for their lunch special.  I ordered hot lemon tea. My tea arrived at the table at room temperature.  It took us quite some time to get our food and when we got it (we both got different steaks) they were both at room temperature.  To give another estimate on warmth, I immediately put the butter under the mashed potatoes (that they came with) and it never melted.  We both ordered medium rare and my steak was not evenly cooked throughout, rare to medium rare patches.  I don't know if the chief was having a bad day, but that was the experience with our main dishes.
The reason for two stars was the semi buffet lunch had a well rounded selection with good flavour.  There were various appetizers and desserts included.

Nice restaurant in Causeway bay's Fashion Walk Food Street. Has good classic steakhouse style of food with everything from salads, steaks and opulent desserts. Very high quality on most of the food and attentive, competent wait staff. Somewhat small portions and lacking a bit in taste for my personal preference, but this is a different style than the offerings tailored to gluttons so that's not a mark against this restaurant.
Relaxing place with good food
I love this place. It's a buffet hybrid. The starters and dessert are buffet, the main course is not. Food is really good too
foods and services are very good
